<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,963,1882]" pageId="12" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,1662,1688]" pageId="12" pageNumber="52">Remarks.</emphasis>
In this species, medial line is absent on forewing, that is different with the other species in the genus. In male genitalia, the species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[730,867,1702,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Gargela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilineata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[730,867,1702,1727]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="52">G. bilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[875,968,1701,1727]" pageId="12" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[875,968,1701,1727]" pageId="12" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but the aedeagus without cornutus and the costal arm is shorter than valva while in 
<taxonomicName box="[666,801,1740,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Gargela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilineata">
<emphasis box="[666,801,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="52">G. bilineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the aedeagus with cornuti and the costal arm is longer than valva.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="52" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,963,1882]" pageId="12" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,343,1817,1843]" pageId="12" pageNumber="52">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[815,906,1817,1842]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="52">albidus</emphasis>
”, corresponding to the white wings of this species.
</paragraph>
